node.text: Adding fall touches to the kitchen!!! Who says your kitchen can’t go all out for fall!! I love bringing in fall colors through the use of kitchen towels and fruit. Pinecones are a great way to add texture and so are wall baskets and wood pieces. Of course I love bringing in touches of fall with some real and faux stems. For fall it’s all about warming up a space. If you want to add a touch of cozy, add the Aria essential oil diffuser. It not only looks good, but helps your kitchen smell like fall! Head to the blog for links to everything!!! Now I just need to sip on a pumpkin spice latte and put on some slippers!!! Happy fall y’all!! #falldecor #fallkitchen #falldecorations #kitchendesign #kitchendecor #homedecor #interiordesign #bhgfall

node.text:
Man these early school mornings are kicking my booty! I had to take a nap today lol! When I say I’m not a morning person, I mean it! I did manage to get some new bathroom decor up in the office bath though! I added a new cute striped shower curtain and some clean fresh towels from @walmart home!! They are from their Gap home collection. You know I can’t resist stripes, so this pretty blue and white shower curtain caught my eye! And the towels have a nice texture to them. I like adding a shower curtain to the bathroom to help add a little bit of softness. To say I’m impressed with @walmart home decor selection is an under statement! They have quality items, at reasonable prices. Swipe to see more.

node.text:
Well hello beautiful rug!! Well hello beautiful pillows!!! Did a spruce up in the loft with some items from @jossandmain Fall Edit!!! The Joss & Main’s fall edit catalog is here, with 5 home trends inspired by dressing up after a year of staying home. Ok fall is my favorite season to decorate for because I love earth tones!! I especially love pairing earth tones with neutrals! I got a couple good neutral pillows and then paired them with my colorful ones. That way you can keep the neutrals out all year, and change out the colorful ones as you want. This gorgeous rug is a good colorful rug, but still neutral enough to go with a variety of decor. I have shopped @jossandmain for many years for myself and my clients! Their selection and quality never disappoint. Bonus!! All the items ship fast and free!!!! node.text: Let’s make the easiest kid’s sandwiches!!! Grab a loaf of French bread, slice down the middle, add your meat, add your condiments, slice into small pieces, place in ziplock baggie, pop in the fridge! Let the kids munch on these throughout the day!! These are also great for school lunches!  Bonus these are inexpensive to make!  #foodhacks #foodreels #recipes #kidslunchideas #kidssnacks #sandwhich
